// =============================================================================
// owl2_fs — OWL 2 Functional-Style Syntax framework axiom package (VVA §21)
// =============================================================================
//

// Verum's trusted boundary for OWL 2 Direct Semantics. Encodes the
// 10 Shkotin 2019 (`internal/OWL2.DS2HOL.pdf`) tables verbatim as
// `@framework(owl2_fs, ...)` axioms — every operator the W3C OWL 2
// Functional-Style Syntax recognises gets exactly one named axiom
// in this package.
//

// Sub-modules (Shkotin 2019 §X.Y / Table Z):
//

//  types — primitive sorts (Individual=o, Literal=d) +
//  count_o quantifier-of-quantity primitive
//  object_property — §2.2.1 Table 1: ObjectInverseOf
//  data_range — §2.2.2 Table 3: 5 data-range constructors
//  class_expr — §2.2.3 Table 4: 24 class-expression constructors
//  class_axiom — §2.3.1 Table 5: 4 class-expression axioms
//  object_property_axiom — §2.3.2 Table 6: 14 object-property axioms
//  data_property_axiom — §2.3.3 Table 7: 6 data-property axioms
//  datatype_definition — §2.3.4 Table 8: 1 datatype-definition axiom
//  key — §2.3.5 Table 9: HasKey (NAMED restriction)
//  assertion — §2.3.6 Table 10: 7 ABox assertions
//

// Total axiom count : 64 + 1 (count_o_spec) = 65 trusted operators,
// each with a load-bearing HOL `ensures` clause (see V2 status below).
//

// **V2 status (current).** All 65 axioms now carry their verbatim
// W3C OWL 2 DS §X.Y / Shkotin 2019 Table-N HOL-definition bodies as
// concrete `ensures` clauses over the `Interpretation` protocol — see
// `class_axiom.vr` (4), `class_expr.vr` (25), `object_property_axiom.vr`
// (14), `data_property_axiom.vr` (6), `data_range.vr` (5),
// `datatype_definition.vr` (1), `key.vr` (1), `assertion.vr` (7),
// `object_property.vr` (1), `types.vr` (1, count_o_spec). Earlier
// `ensures true;` placeholders are replaced; only the historical
// notes in this file's body retain that wording for context.
//

// **V1 baseline (preserved).** Each axiom ships as a trusted-
// boundary marker that `verum audit --framework-axioms --by-lineage
// owl2_fs` enumerates exactly. V1 → V2 transition was non-breaking:
// every previously-named axiom kept its name and arity; only the
// `ensures` clause grew from `true` to the load-bearing HOL body.
// Downstream cogs that bound to V1 names continue to compile.
//

// **Why this matters for the SMT dispatch path.** With the HOL bodies
// in place, `@verify(certified)` obligations stated in OWL 2 terms
// route through the standard kernel + SMT pipeline: the obligation
// inlines the relevant axiom's `ensures` clause, the SMT backend
// (CVC5 FMF for OWL 2 DL) decides it, and the proof certificate
// replays through both kernels at validator load time.
//

// References:
//  - VVA spec §21 — `docs/architecture/verification-architecture.md`
//  - Shkotin 2019 — `internal/OWL2.DS2HOL.pdf`
//  - W3C OWL 2 DS Rec — https://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-semantics/
//  - W3C OWL 2 FS Rec — https://www.w3.org/TR/owl2-syntax/
// =============================================================================

public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.types;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.count;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.object_property;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.data_range;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.class_expr;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.class_axiom;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.object_property_axiom;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.data_property_axiom;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.datatype_definition;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.key;
public mount core.math.frameworks.owl2_fs.assertion;
